Good question — removing a finalizer is often needed when a resource is stuck in Terminating state.


---

🧠 What is a Finalizer (quick)

A finalizer is a protection mechanism in Kubernetes that:

Prevents deletion until cleanup is done

Example (your PVC):


finalizers:
- kubernetes.io/pvc-protection


---

🔴 When to Remove Finalizer

Only remove if:

Resource stuck in Terminating

Cleanup already done OR not needed

You understand it may leave orphan resources (like storage)



---

✅ Method 1: Using oc patch (Easiest)

🔹 For PVC

oc patch pvc bscf9901-db-pvc -n cnf-bscf -p '{"metadata":{"finalizers":null}}' --type=merge


---

🔹 For PV

oc patch pv <pv-name> -p '{"metadata":{"finalizers":null}}' --type=merge


---

🔹 For Pod

oc patch pod <pod-name> -n <namespace> -p '{"metadata":{"finalizers":null}}' --type=merge


---

✅ Method 2: Using YAML Edit

oc edit pvc bscf9901-db-pvc -n cnf-bscf

Find:

finalizers:
- kubernetes.io/pvc-protection

👉 Change to:

finalizers: []

Save & exit


---

✅ Method 3: Force Delete (alternative)

oc delete pvc bscf9901-db-pvc -n cnf-bscf --force --grace-period=0

⚠️ But this does NOT always remove finalizers → patch is better


---

🚨 Important Warnings

⚠️ For Storage (VERY IMPORTANT)

If you remove finalizer on:

PVC / PV backed by Ceph (ODF)


👉 It may:

Leave volume orphaned in Ceph

Cause future mount issues



